This paper deals with anomaly detection in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also uses a conditional generative adversarial network (GAN) for the anomaly detection task, which is a popular technique in machine learning and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training the GAN using a semi-supervised learning paradigm, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
